%md
## 1) Calculate the average rating for each movie.

msg.data: 1) Calculate the average rating for each movie.

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT 
    t.title,
    AVG(r.rating) as avg_rating
FROM ratings r
JOIN titles t
ON r.movieID = t.movieID
GROUP BY t.title
ORDER BY avg_rating DESC
LIMIT 20

%md
## 3) Find the users who have rated at least 50 movies and identify their favourite movie genres.

msg.data: 3) Find the users who have rated at least 50 movies and identify their favourite movie genres.

paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window

// Filter users with ≥ 50 ratings
val filteredUsers = ratingsDF
  .groupBy("userID")
  .count()
  .filter($"count" >= 50)
  .select("userID")

// Join ratings and movies
val filteredRatings = ratingsDF
  .join(filteredUsers, Seq("userID"))
  .join(moviesDF, Seq("movieID"))

// Create an array of (genre, value) structs
val genreColumns = Seq(
  "unknown", "action", "adventure", "animation", "children", "comedy", "crime",
  "documentary", "drama", "fantasy", "filmNoir", "horror", "musical",
  "mystery", "romance", "sciFi", "thriller", "war", "western"
)

val genreArray = array(
  genreColumns.map(c => struct(lit(c).alias("genre"), col(c).alias("value"))): _*
)

// Create a new dataframe from the array above and the filtered ratings
val meltedGenres = filteredRatings
  .withColumn("genre_struct", explode(genreArray))
  .select($"userID", $"genre_struct.genre", $"genre_struct.value")
  .filter($"value" === 1)

// Count genre preferences per user
val genreCounts = meltedGenres
  .groupBy("userID", "genre")
  .count()

// Get top genre per user
val windowSpec = Window.partitionBy("userID").orderBy(desc("count"))

val favoriteGenres = genreCounts
  .withColumn("rank", row_number().over(windowSpec))
  .filter($"rank" === 1)
  .select("userID", "genre", "count")

favoriteGenres.orderBy(desc("count")).show()
